author: Inside Edition
description: A mother and her daughter, both nurses, battled to save a state trooper who had been shot. The life-or-death drama started when the trooper pulled over a pickup truck in Kentucky. The trooper's bodycam captured the moment he was shot in the leg. The good Samaritan nurses happened to be passing by, and came to the trooper's aid. They applied a tourniquet using a belt, and tried to keep the injured officer conscious.
title: Mother-Daughter Nurse Duo Saves Kentucky Trooper's Life

author: Inside Edition
description: A new apocalyptic thriller about the threat of nuclear war is sending shockwaves among film viewers. "House of Dynamite" is directed by Kathryn Bigelow, and stars Idris Elba as the president. It imagines the chilling minute-by-minute response by the U.S. government as a nuclear warhead bears down on the country. The film shows the president rushed onto a chopper followed by his military aide carrying the so-called "nuclear football," containing launch codes for a nuclear attack.
title: Could 'House Of Dynamite' Nuclear Attack Happen?

author: Inside Edition
description: TV sports analyst Stephen A. Smith caused an uproar after accusing President Donald Trump of targeting sports figures as revenge for opposing him. But FBI Director Kash Patel, who announced the arrests of 31 people in the gambling scandal, fired back on Fox News. America was stunned by the arrests of NBA Hall of Famer Chauncey Billups, the Miami Heat's Terry Rozier, and former Cleveland Cavaliers' Damon Jones along with accused mobsters.
title: Fire And Fury In Wake Of NBA Gambling Scandal

author: Inside Edition
description: A stream of trucks is hauling the debris from the White House's east wing to the East Potomac Golf Links, a public golf course on an island in the Potomac. Inside Edition producer Michelle Sigona saw trucks driving to the golf course and dumping debris to form hills that will become integrated in the course over time. There are growing concerns Friday about what else might be in the rubble. Environmental scientist Jerry Roseman says there is a high possibility of it containing toxic material.
title: White House's East Wing Debris Is Being Dumped On Public Golf Course

author: Inside Edition
description: It was a race against time to rescue a puppy stuck between two boulders, as little Zoe could be heard yelping in fear. As luck would have it, the dog owner's neighbor just happened to be a fire fighter, and he called in the cavalry. Fire fighters tried to use a hose, but that didn't work. Nor did the jaws of life. Finally, they used inflatable air bags to move the boulders. Zoe's owner was so excited that their dog was freed that they dropped their camera!
title: Puppy Rescued From Between Two Boulders

author: Inside Edition
description: Mary Sickler took the state at the Miss USA Pageant with dark, voluminous hair. But just moments later, Mary, who is Miss Nevada, appeared in the preliminary evening gown competition looking very different. Her long hair was gone, replaced by a bejeweled head covering. The 22-year-old has alopecia, an autoimmune condition that causes hair loss. She only started losing her hair 10 months ago, and now Mary's secret is officially out.
title: Miss Nevada Bravely Reveals Secret On Stage At Miss USA Pageant

author: Inside Edition
description: It was a final bow on an historic career as Misty Copeland performed her last show with the American Ballet Theatre in New York.
title: Misty Copeland Says Goodbye To The Stage #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: An actress has died of a rare disease. Isabelle Tate died on October 19th of Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease. Tate appeared in the pilot episode of ABC's '911: Nashville.' Her agency announced the news of her passing saying she had recently returned to acting and 911 was the first series she auditioned for. Aside from her acting aspirations, she had a love of animals and spent many hours volunteering at shelters in her hometown of Nashville. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: '911: Nashville' Actress Isabelle Tate Dies Of Rare Disease At 23

author: Inside Edition
description: Patrick Sullivan, his wife Cynthia, and their son Tyler sailed from Cape Cod last weekend and anchored off the coast on Naushon Island.
title: Family Rescued From Island After Boat Fire #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: An Arizona father arrested after leaving his 2-year-old daughter in a hot car to die has pleaded guilty to her murder.
title: Father Pleads Guilty To Daughter's Hot Car Murder #shorts
